Name: botlib
Version: 46
Summary: Framework to program bots
Home-page: https://bitbucket.org/bthate/botlib2
Author: Bart Thate
Author-email: bthate@dds.nl
License: MIT
Description-Content-Type: UNKNOWN
Description: .. raw: <html>
        
            <br><br>
        
        BOTLIB is a python3 framework you can use to program bots. It makes it 
        possible to program your own module enabling your own commands and contains serveral modules that can be used to program bots.
        
        BOTLIB has a MIT no-clause license.
        
        install
        =======
        
        you might need to do the following if the bot doesn't work:
        
        ::
        
          export PYTHONPATH="."
          export PYTHONIOENCODING="utf-8"
        
        download
        ========
        
        clone the source:
        
        :: 
        
          hg clone https://bitbucket.org/bthate/botlib2
          cd botlib2
          sudo python3 setup.py install --user
        
        another option is to download with pip3:
        
        ::
        
          pip3 install botlib --upgrade
        
        programming
        ===========
        
        user programmed modules are read from the ~/.mods directory, you can put your .py files over there.
        
        example:
        
        ::
        
          def hi(event):
              event.reply("hi %s" % event.origin)
        
